{"parse":{"title":"International Clown Week","pageid":28278295,"revid":860093091,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>International Clown Week</b> is celebrated each year during the week of August 1-7.\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Clown\" title=\"Clown\">Clown</a> groups often celebrate the week with special activities such as performing volunteer shows<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> or having their local mayor declare the week as a city celebration to coincide with the national and international clown week.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Clown_Week&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Clown Week was celebrated on a limited scale in the 1950s. In 1966 the first International Clown Week chairman, Frank \"Kelly the Clown\" Kelly, was appointed by Ray Bickford, president of Clown Club of America. In 1967 Clown Club of America members were urged to write to their congressmen and senators requesting a <a href=\"/wiki/Presidential_proclamation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Presidential proclamation\">presidential proclamation</a> naming August 1\u20137 as National Clown Week. In 1969 a resolution was introduced. After clowns met with Senator John McClellan of Arkansas who was chairman of the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Senate\" title=\"United States Senate\">United States Senate</a> subcommittee on Observances and Holidays success was finally achieved.\n</p><p>Concurrently, Bill \"Boom-Boom\" Baily, was an original member of Clowns of America when it was founded in 1967. Baily was named the U.S. Chairman of National Clown Week for that organization. \n</p><p>Because each year a chairman had to be chosen in each state to ask their <a href=\"/wiki/Governor\" title=\"Governor\">governor</a> to issue a proclamation honoring National Clown Week, Bill pushed for National Clown Week publicity. He convinced Congressman Garmatz of Maryland and Congressman Myers of Indiana to introduce a joint resolution in Congress establishing National Clown Week as an annual event.  He lobbied the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Congress\" title=\"United States Congress\">United States Congress</a> and organized a visit by clowns to the senate building in <a href=\"/wiki/Washington,_D.C.\" title=\"Washington, D.C.\">Washington, D.C.</a>\n</p><p>On October 8, 1970, Public Law 91-443 under the 91st Congress, JJR 26 was passed by both the House and Senate and was sent to President <a href=\"/wiki/Richard_Nixon\" title=\"Richard Nixon\">Richard Nixon</a> for his signature.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>   \n</p><p>The joint resolution was signed into law by President Nixon on August 2, 1971.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Many clown organizations have an international constituency<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and over time the National Clown Week has expanded to be International Clown Week.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Clown_Week&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dailyrecord.com/article/20100731/ENT/100729059/1005/NEWS01/Dover+museum+celebrates+National+Clown+Week+with+special+event\">Typical Clown Week Event</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://saratogian.com/articles/2010/08/04/news/doc4c599abe05e8f494535821.txt\">Mayor Proclaiming Clown Week</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.internationalclownweek.org/how%20it%20all%20began%20international%20clown%20week%20history.shtml\">International Clown Week Website</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=76042\">President Nixon's Resolution calling for Clown Week</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.coai.org/\">Clowns of America International</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.clownscanada.com/\">Clowns of Canada</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.clowns-international.com/\">Clowns International</a>, and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.worldclown.com\">World Clown Association</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=International_Clown_Week&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2275\nCached time: 20180918085020\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.040 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.047 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 135/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 356/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 88/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 2295/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.005/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 525 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   31.819      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   31.819      1 -total\n  7.39%    2.350      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:28278295-0!canonical and timestamp 20180918085019 and revision id 860093091\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Clowning"},{"sortkey":"","*":"August_observances"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Thematic_weeks_in_the_United_States"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Clown"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Governor"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Presidential proclamation"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Richard Nixon"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"United States Congress"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"United States Senate"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Washington, D.C."}],"templates":[{"ns":10,"exists":"","*":"Template:Reflist"},{"ns":10,"exists":"","*":"Template:Main other"},{"ns":828,"exists":"","*":"Module:Check for unknown parameters"}],"images":[],"externallinks":["http://www.dailyrecord.com/article/20100731/ENT/100729059/1005/NEWS01/Dover+museum+celebrates+National+Clown+Week+with+special+event","http://saratogian.c